comments.body:
Still hitting this on `exceljs@4.4.0` with the EFRAG VSME Digital Template v1.1.0 — a publicly downloadable Excel template used by EU SMEs for the new VSME sustainability disclosure standard ([efrag.org](https://www.efrag.org/)). Same stack as the original report: `renderExpression` → `model.formulae[0]` undefined at `cf-rule-xform.js:158`.

The closed #2311 has the same root cause, a one-line fix proposed (`model.formulae?.[0]`), and a community PR from @AndresDSoto. @ericLemanissier already asked to reopen #2311. Adding our voice — this currently blocks VSME report export for every SME using the official EFRAG template through ExcelJS.

Workaround for anyone landing here: walk every cell after populating data and replace formula cells with their cached evaluated result before `writeBuffer()`:

```js
workbook.eachSheet(sheet => {
  sheet.eachRow({ includeEmpty: true }, row => {
    row.eachCell({ includeEmpty: true }, cell => {
      try {
        if (cell.type === ExcelJS.ValueType.Formula) {
          cell.value = cell.value?.result ?? null;
        }
      } catch { /* skip individual bad cells */ }
    });
  });
});
```

Note: don't read `cell.formula` itself in this sweep — the getter calls `slideFormula` which throws on shared-formula cells whose master coord can't be resolved. `cell.type` and `cell.value` are safe.
